00097 /* Unique table and cache management constants */
00098 #define DD_MAX_SUBTABLE_DENSITY 4       /* tells when to resize a subtable */
00099 /* gc when this percent are dead (measured w.r.t. slots, not keys)
00100 ** The first limit (LO) applies normally. The second limit applies when
00101 ** the package believes more space for the unique table (i.e., more dead
00102 ** nodes) would improve performance, and the unique table is not already
00103 ** too large.
00104 */
00105 #define DD_GC_PERCENT_LO        DD_MAX_SUBTABLE_DENSITY * 20
00106 #define DD_GC_PERCENT_HI        DD_MAX_SUBTABLE_DENSITY * 100
00107 #define DD_MIN_HIT              30      /* resize cache when hit ratio
00108                                            above this percentage (default) */
00109 #define DD_MAX_LOOSE_FRACTION   8 /* 1 / (max fraction of memory used for
00110                                      unique table in fast growth mode) */
00111 #define DD_MAX_CACHE_FRACTION   4 /* 1 / (max fraction of memory used for
00112                                      computed table if resizing enabled) */

00136 /* Hooks in CUDD are functions that the application registers with the
00137 ** manager so that they are called at appropriate times. The functions
00138 ** are passed the manager as argument; they should return 1 if
00139 ** successful and 0 otherwise.
00140 */
00141 typedef struct DdHook {         /* hook list element */
00142     int (*f) ARGS((DdManager *, void *));       /* function to be called */
00143     struct DdHook *next;        /* next element in the list */
00144 } DdHook;
